{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Pat Mitchell: What is the story of this pin?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2000,"text":"Madeleine Albright: This is \"Breaking the Glass Ceiling.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":4000,"text":"PM: Oh."},{"time":7000,"text":"That was well chosen, I would say, for TEDWomen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":10000,"text":"MA: Most of the time I spend when I get up in the morning"},{"time":12000,"text":"is trying to figure out what is going to happen."},{"time":14000,"text":"And none of this pin stuff would have happened"},{"time":16000,"text":"if it hadn't been for Saddam Hussein."},{"time":18000,"text":"I'll tell you what happened."},{"time":20000,"text":"I went to the United Nations as an ambassador,"},{"time":23000,"text":"and it was after the Gulf War,"},{"time":25000,"text":"and I was an instructed ambassador."},{"time":27000,"text":"And the cease-fire had been translated"},{"time":29000,"text":"into a series of sanctions resolutions,"},{"time":32000,"text":"and my instructions"},{"time":34000,"text":"were to say perfectly terrible things about Saddam Hussein constantly,"},{"time":37000,"text":"which he deserved -- he had invaded another country."},{"time":40000,"text":"And so all of a sudden, a poem appeared in the papers in Baghdad"},{"time":43000,"text":"comparing me to many things,"},{"time":45000,"text":"but among them an \"unparalleled serpent.\""},{"time":48000,"text":"And so I happened to have a snake pin."},{"time":50000,"text":"So I wore it when we talked about Iraq."},{"time":52000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":54000,"text":"And when I went out to meet the press,"},{"time":56000,"text":"they zeroed in, said, \"Why are you wearing that snake pin?\""},{"time":58000,"text":"I said, \"Because Saddam Hussein compared me to an unparalleled serpent.\""},{"time":61000,"text":"And then I thought, well this is fun."},{"time":63000,"text":"So I went out and I bought a lot of pins"},{"time":66000,"text":"that would, in fact, reflect"},{"time":68000,"text":"what I thought we were going to do on any given day."},{"time":70000,"text":"So that's how it all started."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72000,"text":"PM: So how large is the collection?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":74000,"text":"MA: Pretty big."},{"time":76000,"text":"It's now traveling."},{"time":78000,"text":"At the moment it's in Indianapolis,"},{"time":80000,"text":"but it was at the Smithsonian."},{"time":82000,"text":"And it goes with a book that says, \"Read My Pins.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":85000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":87000,"text":"PM: So is this a good idea."},{"time":90000,"text":"I remember when you were the first woman"},{"time":92000,"text":"as Secretary of State,"},{"time":94000,"text":"and there was a lot of conversation always"},{"time":96000,"text":"about what you were wearing,"},{"time":98000,"text":"how you looked --"},{"time":100000,"text":"the thing that happens to a lot of women,"},{"time":102000,"text":"especially if they're the first in a position."},{"time":105000,"text":"So how do you feel about that -- the whole --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":108000,"text":"MA: Well, it's pretty irritating actually"},{"time":110000,"text":"because nobody ever describes what a man is wearing."},{"time":113000,"text":"But people did pay attention to what clothes I had."},{"time":116000,"text":"What was interesting was that,"},{"time":118000,"text":"before I went up to New York as U.N. ambassador,"},{"time":120000,"text":"I talked to Jeane Kirkpatrick, who'd been ambassador before me,"},{"time":123000,"text":"and she said, \"You've got to get rid of your professor clothes."},{"time":126000,"text":"Go out and look like a diplomat.\""},{"time":128000,"text":"So that did give me a lot of opportunities to go shopping."},{"time":131000,"text":"But still, there were all kinds of questions"},{"time":134000,"text":"about -- \"did you wear a hat?\" \"How short was your skirt?\""},{"time":137000,"text":"And one of the things --"},{"time":139000,"text":"if you remember Condoleezza Rice was at some event and she wore boots,"},{"time":142000,"text":"and she got criticized over that."},{"time":144000,"text":"And no guy ever gets criticized. But that's the least of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147000,"text":"PM: It is, for all of us, men and women,"},{"time":150000,"text":"finding our ways of defining our roles,"},{"time":153000,"text":"and doing them in ways that make a difference in the world"},{"time":156000,"text":"and shape the future."},{"time":158000,"text":"How did you handle that balance"},{"time":161000,"text":"between being the tough diplomatic"},{"time":164000,"text":"and strong voice of this country"},{"time":167000,"text":"to the rest of the world"},{"time":169000,"text":"and also how you felt about yourself"},{"time":171000,"text":"as a mother, a grandmother, nurturing ..."},{"time":174000,"text":"and so how did you handle that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":176000,"text":"MA: Well the interesting part was I was asked"},{"time":178000,"text":"what it was like to be the first woman Secretary of State"},{"time":180000,"text":"a few minutes after I'd been named."},{"time":182000,"text":"And I said, \"Well I've been a woman for 60 years,"},{"time":184000,"text":"but I've only been Secretary of State for a few minutes.\""},{"time":187000,"text":"So it evolved."},{"time":189000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":191000,"text":"But basically I love being a woman."},{"time":193000,"text":"And so what happened --"},{"time":195000,"text":"and I think there will probably be some people in the audience"},{"time":197000,"text":"that will identify with this --"},{"time":199000,"text":"I went to my first meeting, first at the U.N.,"},{"time":202000,"text":"and that's when this all started,"},{"time":204000,"text":"because that is a very male organization."},{"time":207000,"text":"And I'm sitting there -- there are 15 members of the Security Council --"},{"time":210000,"text":"so 14 men sat there staring at me,"},{"time":214000,"text":"and I thought -- well you know how we all are."},{"time":216000,"text":"You want to get the feeling of the room,"},{"time":218000,"text":"and \"do people like me?\""},{"time":220000,"text":"and \"will I really say something intelligent?\""},{"time":222000,"text":"And all of a sudden I thought, \"Well, wait a minute."},{"time":225000,"text":"I am sitting behind a sign that says 'The United States,'"},{"time":228000,"text":"and if I don't speak today"},{"time":230000,"text":"then the voice of the United States will not be heard,\""},{"time":233000,"text":"and it was the first time that I had that feeling"},{"time":235000,"text":"that I had to step out of myself"},{"time":237000,"text":"in my normal, reluctant female mode"},{"time":241000,"text":"and decide that I had to speak on behalf of our country."},{"time":244000,"text":"And so that happened more at various times,"},{"time":247000,"text":"but I really think that there was a great advantage in many ways"},{"time":251000,"text":"to being a woman."},{"time":253000,"text":"I think we are a lot better"},{"time":255000,"text":"at personal relationships,"},{"time":257000,"text":"and then have the capability obviously"},{"time":259000,"text":"of telling it like it is when it's necessary."},{"time":262000,"text":"But I have to tell you, I have my youngest granddaughter,"},{"time":264000,"text":"when she turned seven last year,"},{"time":266000,"text":"said to her mother, my daughter,"},{"time":268000,"text":"\"So what's the big deal about Grandma Maddie being Secretary of State?"},{"time":271000,"text":"Only girls are Secretary of State.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":273000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":275000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":284000,"text":"PM: Because in her lifetime -- MA: That would be so."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288000,"text":"PM: What a change that is."},{"time":290000,"text":"As you travel now all over the world,"},{"time":293000,"text":"which you do frequently,"},{"time":295000,"text":"how do you assess"},{"time":297000,"text":"this global narrative around the story of women and girls?"},{"time":300000,"text":"Where are we?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":302000,"text":"MA: I think we're slowly changing,"},{"time":304000,"text":"but obviously there are whole pockets"},{"time":306000,"text":"in countries where nothing is different."},{"time":308000,"text":"And therefore it means that we have to remember"},{"time":311000,"text":"that, while many of us have had huge opportunities --"},{"time":314000,"text":"and Pat, you have been a real leader in your field --"},{"time":317000,"text":"is that there are a lot of women"},{"time":319000,"text":"that are not capable"},{"time":321000,"text":"of worrying and taking care of themselves"},{"time":323000,"text":"and understanding that women have to help other women."},{"time":326000,"text":"And so what I have felt --"},{"time":328000,"text":"and I have looked at this"},{"time":330000,"text":"from a national security issue --"},{"time":332000,"text":"when I was Secretary of State, I decided"},{"time":335000,"text":"that women's issues had to be central to American foreign policy,"},{"time":338000,"text":"not just because I'm a feminist,"},{"time":340000,"text":"but because I believe that societies are better off"},{"time":344000,"text":"when women are politically and economically empowered,"},{"time":347000,"text":"that values are passed down,"},{"time":349000,"text":"the health situation is better,"},{"time":352000,"text":"education is better,"},{"time":354000,"text":"there is greater economic prosperity."},{"time":356000,"text":"So I think that it behooves us --"},{"time":359000,"text":"those of us that live in various countries"},{"time":362000,"text":"where we do have economic and political voice --"},{"time":365000,"text":"that we need to help other women."},{"time":367000,"text":"And I really dedicated myself to that,"},{"time":369000,"text":"both at the U.N. and then as Secretary of State."}]},{"cues":[{"time":372000,"text":"PM: And did you get pushback"},{"time":374000,"text":"from making that a central tenant of foreign policy?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":377000,"text":"MA: From some people."},{"time":379000,"text":"I think that they thought that it was a soft issue."},{"time":382000,"text":"The bottom line that I decided"},{"time":384000,"text":"was actually women's issues are the hardest issues,"},{"time":387000,"text":"because they are the ones that have to do with life and death"},{"time":390000,"text":"in so many aspects,"},{"time":392000,"text":"and because, as I said,"},{"time":394000,"text":"it is really central to the way that we think about things."},{"time":397000,"text":"Now for instance,"},{"time":399000,"text":"some of the wars that took place"},{"time":401000,"text":"when I was in office,"},{"time":403000,"text":"a lot of them, the women were the main victims of it."},{"time":406000,"text":"For instance, when I started,"},{"time":408000,"text":"there were wars in the Balkans."},{"time":411000,"text":"The women in Bosnia were being raped."},{"time":414000,"text":"We then managed to set up a war crimes tribunal"},{"time":417000,"text":"to deal specifically with those kinds of issues."},{"time":420000,"text":"And by the way, one of the things that I did at that stage"},{"time":423000,"text":"was, I had just arrived at the U.N.,"},{"time":426000,"text":"and when I was there, there were 183 countries in the U.N."},{"time":429000,"text":"Now there are 192."},{"time":431000,"text":"But it was one of the first times that I didn't have to cook lunch myself."},{"time":434000,"text":"So I said to my assistant,"},{"time":436000,"text":"\"Invite the other women permanent representatives.\""},{"time":439000,"text":"And I thought when I'd get to my apartment"},{"time":441000,"text":"that there'd be a lot of women there."},{"time":443000,"text":"I get there, and there are six other women, out of 183."},{"time":446000,"text":"So the countries that had women representatives"},{"time":449000,"text":"were Canada, Kazakhstan, Philippines,"},{"time":451000,"text":"Trinidad Tobago, Jamaica,"},{"time":453000,"text":"Lichtenstein and me."},{"time":456000,"text":"So being an American, I decided to set up a caucus."},{"time":459000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":461000,"text":"And so we set it up,"},{"time":463000,"text":"and we called ourselves the G7."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":467000,"text":"PM: Is that \"Girl 7?\" MA: Girl 7."}]},{"cues":[{"time":469000,"text":"And we lobbied"},{"time":471000,"text":"on behalf of women's issues."},{"time":473000,"text":"So we managed to get two women judges"},{"time":476000,"text":"on this war crimes tribunal."},{"time":478000,"text":"And then what happened"},{"time":480000,"text":"was that they were able to declare that rape was a weapon of war,"},{"time":483000,"text":"that it was against humanity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":485000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":490000,"text":"PM: So when you look around the world"},{"time":492000,"text":"and you see that, in many cases --"},{"time":494000,"text":"certainly in the Western world --"},{"time":496000,"text":"women are evolving into more leadership positions,"},{"time":499000,"text":"and even other places"},{"time":501000,"text":"some barriers are being brought down,"},{"time":504000,"text":"but there's still so much violence,"},{"time":507000,"text":"still so many problems,"},{"time":509000,"text":"and yet we hear there are more women"},{"time":511000,"text":"at the negotiating tables."},{"time":513000,"text":"Now you were at those negotiating tables"},{"time":515000,"text":"when they weren't, when there was maybe you --"},{"time":518000,"text":"one voice, maybe one or two others."},{"time":520000,"text":"Do you believe, and can you tell us why,"},{"time":523000,"text":"there is going to be a significant shift"},{"time":526000,"text":"in things like violence"},{"time":528000,"text":"and peace and conflict and resolution"},{"time":531000,"text":"on a sustainable basis?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":533000,"text":"MA: Well I do think, when there are more women,"},{"time":536000,"text":"that the tone of the conversation changes,"},{"time":540000,"text":"and also the goals of the conversation change."},{"time":543000,"text":"But it doesn't mean that the whole world"},{"time":545000,"text":"would be a lot better"},{"time":547000,"text":"if it were totally run by women."},{"time":549000,"text":"If you think that, you've forgotten high school."},{"time":552000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":555000,"text":"But the bottom line"},{"time":557000,"text":"is that there is a way,"},{"time":559000,"text":"when there are more women at the table,"},{"time":562000,"text":"that there's an attempt"},{"time":564000,"text":"to develop some understanding."},{"time":566000,"text":"So for instance, what I did when I went to Burundi,"},{"time":569000,"text":"we'd got Tutsi and Hutu women together"},{"time":572000,"text":"to talk about some of the problems"},{"time":574000,"text":"that had taken place in Rwanda."},{"time":576000,"text":"And so I think the capability of women"},{"time":579000,"text":"to put themselves --"},{"time":581000,"text":"I think we're better about putting ourselves into the other guy's shoes"},{"time":584000,"text":"and having more empathy."},{"time":586000,"text":"I think it helps in terms of the support"},{"time":589000,"text":"if there are other women in the room."}]},{"cues":[{"time":591000,"text":"When I was Secretary of State,"},{"time":593000,"text":"there were only 13 other women foreign ministers."},{"time":596000,"text":"And so it was nice when one of them would show up."},{"time":599000,"text":"For instance, she is now the president of Finland,"},{"time":602000,"text":"but Tarja Halonen was the foreign minister of Finland"},{"time":605000,"text":"and, at a certain stage, head of the European Union."},{"time":608000,"text":"And it was really terrific."},{"time":610000,"text":"Because one of the things I think you'll understand."},{"time":612000,"text":"We went to a meeting,"},{"time":614000,"text":"and the men in my delegation,"},{"time":616000,"text":"when I would say, \"Well I feel we should do something about this,\""},{"time":619000,"text":"and they'd say, \"What do you mean, you feel?\""},{"time":622000,"text":"And so then Tarja was sitting across the table from me."},{"time":625000,"text":"And all of a sudden we were talking about arms control,"},{"time":628000,"text":"and she said, \"Well I feel we should do this.\""},{"time":630000,"text":"And my male colleagues kind of got it all of a sudden."},{"time":633000,"text":"But I think it really does help"},{"time":635000,"text":"to have a critical mass of women"},{"time":638000,"text":"in a series of foreign policy positions."},{"time":641000,"text":"The other thing that I think is really important:"},{"time":644000,"text":"A lot of national security policy"},{"time":646000,"text":"isn't just about foreign policy,"},{"time":648000,"text":"but it's about budgets, military budgets,"},{"time":651000,"text":"and how the debts of countries work out."},{"time":654000,"text":"So if you have women"},{"time":656000,"text":"in a variety of foreign policy posts,"},{"time":659000,"text":"they can support each other"},{"time":661000,"text":"when there are budget decisions being made in their own countries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664000,"text":"PM: So how do we get"},{"time":666000,"text":"this balance we're looking for, then, in the world?"},{"time":669000,"text":"More women's voices at the table?"},{"time":671000,"text":"More men who believe"},{"time":673000,"text":"that the balance is best?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":675000,"text":"MA: Well I think one of the things --"},{"time":677000,"text":"I'm chairman of the board of an organization"},{"time":679000,"text":"called the National Democratic Institute"},{"time":681000,"text":"that works to support women candidates."},{"time":684000,"text":"I think that we need"},{"time":686000,"text":"to help in other countries"},{"time":688000,"text":"to train women"},{"time":690000,"text":"to be in political office,"},{"time":692000,"text":"to figure out how they can in fact"},{"time":694000,"text":"develop political voices."},{"time":696000,"text":"I think we also need to be supportive"},{"time":699000,"text":"when businesses are being created"},{"time":702000,"text":"and just make sure that women help each other."},{"time":704000,"text":"Now I have a saying"},{"time":706000,"text":"that I feel very strongly about,"},{"time":708000,"text":"because I am of a certain age"},{"time":710000,"text":"where, when I started in my career,"},{"time":712000,"text":"believe it or not, there were other women who criticized me:"},{"time":715000,"text":"\"Why aren't you in the carpool line?\""},{"time":718000,"text":"or \"Aren't your children suffering"},{"time":720000,"text":"because you're not there all the time?\""},{"time":722000,"text":"And I think we have a tendency to make each other feel guilty."},{"time":725000,"text":"In fact, I think \"guilt\" is every woman's middle name."},{"time":729000,"text":"And so I think what needs to happen"},{"time":731000,"text":"is we need to help each other."},{"time":734000,"text":"And my motto is that there's a special place in hell"},{"time":736000,"text":"for women who don't help each other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":739000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":747000,"text":"PM: Well Secretary Albright, I guess you'll be going to heaven."},{"time":751000,"text":"Thank you for joining us today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":753000,"text":"MA: Thank you all. Thanks Pat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":756000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}